{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-docs-js","path":"/docs/contribute.html","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<h2 id=\"how-to-contribute-from-install-to-pull-request\"><a href=\"#how-to-contribute-from-install-to-pull-request\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>How To Contribute: From Install To Pull-Request</h2>\n<div class=\"gatsby-resp-iframe-wrapper\" style=\"padding-bottom: 56.25%; position: relative; height: 0; overflow: hidden; \" > <div class=\"video\"> <iframe src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/BWBvjkpIaY8\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen style=\" position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; width: 100%; height: 100%; \"></iframe> </div> </div>\n<p>Topics covered in this tutorial:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#setting-up-scandipwa\">Setting up ScandiPWA</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#making-a-contribution-front-end\">Making A Contribution: Front-End</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#making-a-contribution-back-end\">Making A Contribution: Back-End</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"setting-up-scandipwa\"><a href=\"#setting-up-scandipwa\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Setting up ScandiPWA</h2>\n<p>The first thing you need to do is make sure you have <a href=\"https://docs.github.com/en/github/getting-started-with-github/fork-a-repo\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">forked</a> and <a href=\"https://docs.github.com/en/github/creating-cloning-and-archiving-repositories/cloning-a-repository\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">cloned</a> the <code class=\"gatsby-code-text\">scandipwa-base</code> project.</p>\n<p>First, let’s open up the terminal and navigate to the project’s directory.</p>\n<div\n              class=\"gatsby-code-button-container\"\n              data-toaster-id=\"93111723166138220000\"\n              data-toaster-class=\"gatsby-code-button-toaster customToasterClass\"\n              data-toaster-text-class=\"gatsby-code-button-toaster-text customToasterTextClass\"\n              data-toaster-text=\"Copied\"\n              data-toaster-duration=\"3500\"\n              onClick=\"copyToClipboard(`cd ~/Myproject/scandipwa-base/\nls -la # confirm that we're in the right place`, `93111723166138220000`)\"\n            >\n              <div\n                class=\"gatsby-code-button customButtonClass\"\n                data-tooltip=\"\"\n              >\n                Copy<svg class=\"gatsby-code-button-icon\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"><path fill=\"none\" d=\"M0 0h24v24H0V0z\"/><path d=\"M16 1H2v16h2V3h12V1zm-1 4l6 6v12H6V5h9zm-1 7h5.5L14 6.5V12z\"/></svg>\n              </div>\n            </div>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"gatsby-code-bash\"><code class=\"gatsby-code-bash\"><span class=\"token builtin class-name\">cd</span> ~/Myproject/scandipwa-base/\n<span class=\"token function\">ls</span> -la <span class=\"token comment\"># confirm that we're in the right place</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>Previously, in the <a href=\"https://docs.scandipwa.com/docs/linux.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Linux Docker set-up</a> we already created aliases for <code class=\"gatsby-code-text\">docker-compose</code> commands. Here’s a little refresher:</p>\n<div\n              class=\"gatsby-code-button-container\"\n              data-toaster-id=\"20623185334269678000\"\n              data-toaster-class=\"gatsby-code-button-toaster customToasterClass\"\n              data-toaster-text-class=\"gatsby-code-button-toaster-text customToasterTextClass\"\n              data-toaster-text=\"Copied\"\n              data-toaster-duration=\"3500\"\n              onClick=\"copyToClipboard(`# use \\`dc\\` to start without \\`frontend\\` container\nalias dc=&quot;docker-compose -f docker-compose.yml -f docker-compose.local.yml -f docker-compose.ssl.yml&quot;\n\n# use \\`dcf\\` to start with \\`frontend\\` container\nalias dcf=&quot;docker-compose -f docker-compose.yml -f docker-compose.local.yml -f docker-compose.ssl.yml -f docker-compose.frontend.yml&quot;\n\n# use \\`inapp\\` to quickly get inside of the app container\nalias inapp=&quot;docker-compose -f docker-compose.yml -f docker-compose.local.yml -f docker-compose.ssl.yml -f docker-compose.frontend.yml exec -u user app&quot;\n\n# use \\`infront\\` to quickly get inside of the frontend container\nalias infront=&quot;docker-compose -f docker-compose.yml -f docker-compose.local.yml -f docker-compose.ssl.yml -f docker-compose.frontend.yml exec -w /var/www/public/app/design/frontend/Scandiweb/pwa/ frontend&quot;\n\n# use \\`applogs\\` to quickly see the last 100 lines of app container logs\nalias applogs=&quot;docker-compose logs -f --tail=100 app&quot;\n\n# use \\`frontlogs\\` to quickly see the last 100 lines of frontend container logs\nalias frontlogs=&quot;docker-compose -f docker-compose.yml -f docker-compose.local.yml -f docker-compose.ssl.yml -f docker-compose.frontend.yml logs -f --tail=100 frontend&quot;`, `20623185334269678000`)\"\n            >\n              <div\n                class=\"gatsby-code-button customButtonClass\"\n                data-tooltip=\"\"\n              >\n                Copy<svg class=\"gatsby-code-button-icon\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"><path fill=\"none\" d=\"M0 0h24v24H0V0z\"/><path d=\"M16 1H2v16h2V3h12V1zm-1 4l6 6v12H6V5h9zm-1 7h5.5L14 6.5V12z\"/></svg>\n              </div>\n            </div>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"gatsby-code-bash\"><code class=\"gatsby-code-bash\"><span class=\"token comment\"># use `dc` to start without `frontend` container</span>\n<span class=\"token builtin class-name\">alias</span> <span class=\"token assign-left variable\">dc</span><span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"docker-compose -f docker-compose.yml -f docker-compose.local.yml -f docker-compose.ssl.yml\"</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\"># use `dcf` to start with `frontend` container</span>\n<span class=\"token builtin class-name\">alias</span> <span class=\"token assign-left variable\">dcf</span><span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"docker-compose -f docker-compose.yml -f docker-compose.local.yml -f docker-compose.ssl.yml -f docker-compose.frontend.yml\"</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\"># use `inapp` to quickly get inside of the app container</span>\n<span class=\"token builtin class-name\">alias</span> <span class=\"token assign-left variable\">inapp</span><span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"docker-compose -f docker-compose.yml -f docker-compose.local.yml -f docker-compose.ssl.yml -f docker-compose.frontend.yml exec -u user app\"</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\"># use `infront` to quickly get inside of the frontend container</span>\n<span class=\"token builtin class-name\">alias</span> <span class=\"token assign-left variable\">infront</span><span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"docker-compose -f docker-compose.yml -f docker-compose.local.yml -f docker-compose.ssl.yml -f docker-compose.frontend.yml exec -w /var/www/public/app/design/frontend/Scandiweb/pwa/ frontend\"</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\"># use `applogs` to quickly see the last 100 lines of app container logs</span>\n<span class=\"token builtin class-name\">alias</span> <span class=\"token assign-left variable\">applogs</span><span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"docker-compose logs -f --tail=100 app\"</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\"># use `frontlogs` to quickly see the last 100 lines of frontend container logs</span>\n<span class=\"token builtin class-name\">alias</span> <span class=\"token assign-left variable\">frontlogs</span><span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"docker-compose -f docker-compose.yml -f docker-compose.local.yml -f docker-compose.ssl.yml -f docker-compose.frontend.yml logs -f --tail=100 frontend\"</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>We can also look for a specific alias by piping:</p>\n<div\n              class=\"gatsby-code-button-container\"\n              data-toaster-id=\"2169631380025038800\"\n              data-toaster-class=\"gatsby-code-button-toaster customToasterClass\"\n              data-toaster-text-class=\"gatsby-code-button-toaster-text customToasterTextClass\"\n              data-toaster-text=\"Copied\"\n              data-toaster-duration=\"3500\"\n              onClick=\"copyToClipboard(`alias|grep dcf`, `2169631380025038800`)\"\n            >\n              <div\n                class=\"gatsby-code-button customButtonClass\"\n                data-tooltip=\"\"\n              >\n                Copy<svg class=\"gatsby-code-button-icon\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"><path fill=\"none\" d=\"M0 0h24v24H0V0z\"/><path d=\"M16 1H2v16h2V3h12V1zm-1 4l6 6v12H6V5h9zm-1 7h5.5L14 6.5V12z\"/></svg>\n              </div>\n            </div>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"gatsby-code-bash\"><code class=\"gatsby-code-bash\"><span class=\"token builtin class-name\">alias</span><span class=\"token operator\">|</span><span class=\"token function\">grep</span> dcf</code></pre></div>\n<p>If we want to contribute we run:</p>\n<div\n              class=\"gatsby-code-button-container\"\n              data-toaster-id=\"95069322090198760000\"\n              data-toaster-class=\"gatsby-code-button-toaster customToasterClass\"\n              data-toaster-text-class=\"gatsby-code-button-toaster-text customToasterTextClass\"\n              data-toaster-text=\"Copied\"\n              data-toaster-duration=\"3500\"\n              onClick=\"copyToClipboard(`docker-compose -f docker-compose.yml -f docker-compose.local.yml -f docker-compose.ssl.yml -f docker-compose.core.yml`, `95069322090198760000`)\"\n            >\n              <div\n                class=\"gatsby-code-button customButtonClass\"\n                data-tooltip=\"\"\n              >\n                Copy<svg class=\"gatsby-code-button-icon\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"><path fill=\"none\" d=\"M0 0h24v24H0V0z\"/><path d=\"M16 1H2v16h2V3h12V1zm-1 4l6 6v12H6V5h9zm-1 7h5.5L14 6.5V12z\"/></svg>\n              </div>\n            </div>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"gatsby-code-bash\"><code class=\"gatsby-code-bash\">docker-compose -f docker-compose.yml -f docker-compose.local.yml -f docker-compose.ssl.yml -f docker-compose.core.yml</code></pre></div>\n<p>Instead of the <code class=\"gatsby-code-text\">docker-compose.frontend.yml</code> we use <code class=\"gatsby-code-text\">docker-compose.core.yml</code>, where <code class=\"gatsby-code-text\">core</code> stands for contribution.</p>\n<p>Before this, though, we need to make sure that we’ve cloned our theme in the correct place. </p>\n<p>Let’s make a new folder in the <code class=\"gatsby-code-text\">scandipwa-base/src</code> folder. We’ll use this later for composer packages in order to locally connect to them.</p>\n<div\n              class=\"gatsby-code-button-container\"\n              data-toaster-id=\"7872532438056146000\"\n              data-toaster-class=\"gatsby-code-button-toaster customToasterClass\"\n              data-toaster-text-class=\"gatsby-code-button-toaster-text customToasterTextClass\"\n              data-toaster-text=\"Copied\"\n              data-toaster-duration=\"3500\"\n              onClick=\"copyToClipboard(`mkdir src/localmodules`, `7872532438056146000`)\"\n            >\n              <div\n                class=\"gatsby-code-button customButtonClass\"\n                data-tooltip=\"\"\n              >\n                Copy<svg class=\"gatsby-code-button-icon\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"><path fill=\"none\" d=\"M0 0h24v24H0V0z\"/><path d=\"M16 1H2v16h2V3h12V1zm-1 4l6 6v12H6V5h9zm-1 7h5.5L14 6.5V12z\"/></svg>\n              </div>\n            </div>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"gatsby-code-bash\"><code class=\"gatsby-code-bash\"><span class=\"token function\">mkdir</span> src/localmodules</code></pre></div>\n<p>Next, we need to fork the <a href=\"https://github.com/scandipwa/base-theme\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">ScandiPWA base theme</a> and clone it in the <code class=\"gatsby-code-text\">src/localmodules</code> folder.</p>\n<p>After returning to the <code class=\"gatsby-code-text\">scandipwa-base</code> folder we need to run one of our previously aliased commands in order to recreate the docker set-up without front-end:</p>\n<div\n              class=\"gatsby-code-button-container\"\n              data-toaster-id=\"69081870821352190000\"\n              data-toaster-class=\"gatsby-code-button-toaster customToasterClass\"\n              data-toaster-text-class=\"gatsby-code-button-toaster-text customToasterTextClass\"\n              data-toaster-text=\"Copied\"\n              data-toaster-duration=\"3500\"\n              onClick=\"copyToClipboard(`dc up -d`, `69081870821352190000`)\"\n            >\n              <div\n                class=\"gatsby-code-button customButtonClass\"\n                data-tooltip=\"\"\n              >\n                Copy<svg class=\"gatsby-code-button-icon\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"><path fill=\"none\" d=\"M0 0h24v24H0V0z\"/><path d=\"M16 1H2v16h2V3h12V1zm-1 4l6 6v12H6V5h9zm-1 7h5.5L14 6.5V12z\"/></svg>\n              </div>\n            </div>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"gatsby-code-bash\"><code class=\"gatsby-code-bash\"><span class=\"token function\">dc</span> up -d</code></pre></div>\n<p>You can read more about the <code class=\"gatsby-code-text\">docker-compose up</code> command <a href=\"https://docs.docker.com/compose/reference/up/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">here</a>.</p>\n<p>Next, we use <code class=\"gatsby-code-text\">applogs</code> to check-out the last 100 lines of app container logs.</p>\n<p>If you see the <code class=\"gatsby-code-text\">Connection to Redis failed</code> error, you need to force-recreate:</p>\n<div\n              class=\"gatsby-code-button-container\"\n              data-toaster-id=\"9477707591796224000\"\n              data-toaster-class=\"gatsby-code-button-toaster customToasterClass\"\n              data-toaster-text-class=\"gatsby-code-button-toaster-text customToasterTextClass\"\n              data-toaster-text=\"Copied\"\n              data-toaster-duration=\"3500\"\n              onClick=\"copyToClipboard(`dc up -d --force-recreate`, `9477707591796224000`)\"\n            >\n              <div\n                class=\"gatsby-code-button customButtonClass\"\n                data-tooltip=\"\"\n              >\n                Copy<svg class=\"gatsby-code-button-icon\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"><path fill=\"none\" d=\"M0 0h24v24H0V0z\"/><path d=\"M16 1H2v16h2V3h12V1zm-1 4l6 6v12H6V5h9zm-1 7h5.5L14 6.5V12z\"/></svg>\n              </div>\n            </div>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"gatsby-code-bash\"><code class=\"gatsby-code-bash\"><span class=\"token function\">dc</span> up -d --force-recreate</code></pre></div>\n<p>Next we run the <code class=\"gatsby-code-text\">inapp</code> alias to get inside of the app container and <a href=\"https://docs.docker.com/engine/reference/commandline/exec/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">execute</a> an interactive <code class=\"gatsby-code-text\">bash</code> shell in it:</p>\n<div\n              class=\"gatsby-code-button-container\"\n              data-toaster-id=\"72443986774034190000\"\n              data-toaster-class=\"gatsby-code-button-toaster customToasterClass\"\n              data-toaster-text-class=\"gatsby-code-button-toaster-text customToasterTextClass\"\n              data-toaster-text=\"Copied\"\n              data-toaster-duration=\"3500\"\n              onClick=\"copyToClipboard(`inapp bash`, `72443986774034190000`)\"\n            >\n              <div\n                class=\"gatsby-code-button customButtonClass\"\n                data-tooltip=\"\"\n              >\n                Copy<svg class=\"gatsby-code-button-icon\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"><path fill=\"none\" d=\"M0 0h24v24H0V0z\"/><path d=\"M16 1H2v16h2V3h12V1zm-1 4l6 6v12H6V5h9zm-1 7h5.5L14 6.5V12z\"/></svg>\n              </div>\n            </div>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"gatsby-code-bash\"><code class=\"gatsby-code-bash\">inapp <span class=\"token function\">bash</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>Let’s go to the <code class=\"gatsby-code-text\">localmodules/base-theme/</code> folder and run <code class=\"gatsby-code-text\">npm ci</code> to get a clean install of the necessary dependencies.</p>\n<div\n              class=\"gatsby-code-button-container\"\n              data-toaster-id=\"4414995502624719000\"\n              data-toaster-class=\"gatsby-code-button-toaster customToasterClass\"\n              data-toaster-text-class=\"gatsby-code-button-toaster-text customToasterTextClass\"\n              data-toaster-text=\"Copied\"\n              data-toaster-duration=\"3500\"\n              onClick=\"copyToClipboard(`cd localmodules/base-theme/\nnpm ci`, `4414995502624719000`)\"\n            >\n              <div\n                class=\"gatsby-code-button customButtonClass\"\n                data-tooltip=\"\"\n              >\n                Copy<svg class=\"gatsby-code-button-icon\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"><path fill=\"none\" d=\"M0 0h24v24H0V0z\"/><path d=\"M16 1H2v16h2V3h12V1zm-1 4l6 6v12H6V5h9zm-1 7h5.5L14 6.5V12z\"/></svg>\n              </div>\n            </div>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"gatsby-code-bash\"><code class=\"gatsby-code-bash\"><span class=\"token builtin class-name\">cd</span> localmodules/base-theme/\n<span class=\"token function\">npm</span> ci</code></pre></div>\n<p>After installing the modules we can <code class=\"gatsby-code-text\">exit</code> the app for now.\nNow, back in the <code class=\"gatsby-code-text\">scandipwa-base</code> folder run the following to compose the core contribution file:</p>\n<div\n              class=\"gatsby-code-button-container\"\n              data-toaster-id=\"70096111357978260000\"\n              data-toaster-class=\"gatsby-code-button-toaster customToasterClass\"\n              data-toaster-text-class=\"gatsby-code-button-toaster-text customToasterTextClass\"\n              data-toaster-text=\"Copied\"\n              data-toaster-duration=\"3500\"\n              onClick=\"copyToClipboard(`dc -f docker-compose.core.yml up -d`, `70096111357978260000`)\"\n            >\n              <div\n                class=\"gatsby-code-button customButtonClass\"\n                data-tooltip=\"\"\n              >\n                Copy<svg class=\"gatsby-code-button-icon\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"><path fill=\"none\" d=\"M0 0h24v24H0V0z\"/><path d=\"M16 1H2v16h2V3h12V1zm-1 4l6 6v12H6V5h9zm-1 7h5.5L14 6.5V12z\"/></svg>\n              </div>\n            </div>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"gatsby-code-bash\"><code class=\"gatsby-code-bash\"><span class=\"token function\">dc</span> -f docker-compose.core.yml up -d</code></pre></div>\n<p>The <code class=\"gatsby-code-text\">docker-compose.core.yml</code> and <code class=\"gatsby-code-text\">docker-compose.frontend.yml</code> files are the same except for the command <code class=\"gatsby-code-text\">pm2-watch</code>, which in the <code class=\"gatsby-code-text\">core</code> file is replaced by <code class=\"gatsby-code-text\">dev-server-core</code>. </p>\n<p>In <code class=\"gatsby-code-text\">frontend</code> the vendor folders are mapped, however, in <code class=\"gatsby-code-text\">core</code> only the <code class=\"gatsby-code-text\">base-theme</code> is mapped.</p>\n<p>This is because a fall-back mechanism is not needed when you’re contributing - every file in the theme is present.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><strong>Note</strong></p>\n<p>Never use <code class=\"gatsby-code-text\">docker-compose.core.yml</code> and <code class=\"gatsby-code-text\">docker-compose.frontend.yml</code> at the same time.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Next, use <code class=\"gatsby-code-text\">frontlogs</code> to see if <code class=\"gatsby-code-text\">core</code> has compiled and type <code class=\"gatsby-code-text\">scandipwa.local</code> in your browser to check-out if everything is working.</p>\n<p>Next, using whatever text editor you fancy, open the folder <code class=\"gatsby-code-text\">src/local-modules/base-theme</code> and start customising!</p>\n<h2 id=\"making-a-contribution-front-end\"><a href=\"#making-a-contribution-front-end\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Making A Contribution: Front-End</h2>\n<blockquote>\n<p><strong>Note</strong></p>\n<p>Your feature branches must be made from the stable branch.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Note that any contributions must be made to the stable branch, which at this point is <code class=\"gatsby-code-text\">2.x-stable</code>.</p>\n<p>So, after you’ve made the changes save them, <a href=\"https://git-scm.com/docs/git-checkout\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\"><code class=\"gatsby-code-text\">checkout</code></a> to the latest stable <a href=\"https://git-scm.com/docs/git-branch\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">branch</a> and <a href=\"https://git-scm.com/docs/git-stash\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\"><code class=\"gatsby-code-text\">git stash pop</code></a></p>\n<p>The standard sequence after making changes:</p>\n<div\n              class=\"gatsby-code-button-container\"\n              data-toaster-id=\"77014809711438360000\"\n              data-toaster-class=\"gatsby-code-button-toaster customToasterClass\"\n              data-toaster-text-class=\"gatsby-code-button-toaster-text customToasterTextClass\"\n              data-toaster-text=\"Copied\"\n              data-toaster-duration=\"3500\"\n              onClick=\"copyToClipboard(`git stash save\ngit branch <stable-branch-name> HEAD\ngit checkout -b <your-branch-name> # add a descriptive branch name\ngit stash pop`, `77014809711438360000`)\"\n            >\n              <div\n                class=\"gatsby-code-button customButtonClass\"\n                data-tooltip=\"\"\n              >\n                Copy<svg class=\"gatsby-code-button-icon\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"><path fill=\"none\" d=\"M0 0h24v24H0V0z\"/><path d=\"M16 1H2v16h2V3h12V1zm-1 4l6 6v12H6V5h9zm-1 7h5.5L14 6.5V12z\"/></svg>\n              </div>\n            </div>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"gatsby-code-bash\"><code class=\"gatsby-code-bash\"><span class=\"token function\">git</span> stash save\n<span class=\"token function\">git</span> branch <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>stable-branch-name<span class=\"token operator\">></span> HEAD\n<span class=\"token function\">git</span> checkout -b <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>your-branch-name<span class=\"token operator\">></span> <span class=\"token comment\"># add a descriptive branch name</span>\n<span class=\"token function\">git</span> stash pop</code></pre></div>\n<p>Check-out the git reference <a href=\"https://git-scm.com/docs\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">here</a>.</p>\n<p>After doing this you can commit as usual:</p>\n<div\n              class=\"gatsby-code-button-container\"\n              data-toaster-id=\"16328231971187780000\"\n              data-toaster-class=\"gatsby-code-button-toaster customToasterClass\"\n              data-toaster-text-class=\"gatsby-code-button-toaster-text customToasterTextClass\"\n              data-toaster-text=\"Copied\"\n              data-toaster-duration=\"3500\"\n              onClick=\"copyToClipboard(`git add <file-name>\ngit commit -m &quot;your-message&quot;\ngit push\ngit push origin <your-branch-name>`, `16328231971187780000`)\"\n            >\n              <div\n                class=\"gatsby-code-button customButtonClass\"\n                data-tooltip=\"\"\n              >\n                Copy<svg class=\"gatsby-code-button-icon\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"><path fill=\"none\" d=\"M0 0h24v24H0V0z\"/><path d=\"M16 1H2v16h2V3h12V1zm-1 4l6 6v12H6V5h9zm-1 7h5.5L14 6.5V12z\"/></svg>\n              </div>\n            </div>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"gatsby-code-bash\"><code class=\"gatsby-code-bash\"><span class=\"token function\">git</span> <span class=\"token function\">add</span> <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>file-name<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n<span class=\"token function\">git</span> commit -m <span class=\"token string\">\"your-message\"</span>\n<span class=\"token function\">git</span> push\n<span class=\"token function\">git</span> push origin <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>your-branch-name<span class=\"token operator\">></span></code></pre></div>\n<p>After this you should see <your-branch-name> in your GitHub account and create a pull request.\nThen the pull request will be reviewed by our fabulous maintainers and either be approved or closed.</p>\n<h2 id=\"making-a-contribution-back-end\"><a href=\"#making-a-contribution-back-end\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Making A Contribution: Back-End</h2>\n<p>Clone the repo the same way as previously, you can choose e.g. <code class=\"gatsby-code-text\">store-graphql</code>.</p>\n<p>If you want to contribute to one of the back-end features, you have to select a one patch number higher than that of the available ones.</p>\n<p>So if the latest release is 1.0.2, yours will be 1.0.3</p>\n<p>First we need to find out which version we currently have, so let’s enter the container:</p>\n<div\n              class=\"gatsby-code-button-container\"\n              data-toaster-id=\"85036470989374140000\"\n              data-toaster-class=\"gatsby-code-button-toaster customToasterClass\"\n              data-toaster-text-class=\"gatsby-code-button-toaster-text customToasterTextClass\"\n              data-toaster-text=\"Copied\"\n              data-toaster-duration=\"3500\"\n              onClick=\"copyToClipboard(`inapp bash\ncomposer info scandipwa/store-graphql`, `85036470989374140000`)\"\n            >\n              <div\n                class=\"gatsby-code-button customButtonClass\"\n                data-tooltip=\"\"\n              >\n                Copy<svg class=\"gatsby-code-button-icon\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"><path fill=\"none\" d=\"M0 0h24v24H0V0z\"/><path d=\"M16 1H2v16h2V3h12V1zm-1 4l6 6v12H6V5h9zm-1 7h5.5L14 6.5V12z\"/></svg>\n              </div>\n            </div>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"gatsby-code-bash\"><code class=\"gatsby-code-bash\">inapp <span class=\"token function\">bash</span>\n<span class=\"token function\">composer</span> info scandipwa/store-graphql</code></pre></div>\n<p>At this current time latest version is 1.0.2</p>\n<div\n              class=\"gatsby-code-button-container\"\n              data-toaster-id=\"69286516361667580000\"\n              data-toaster-class=\"gatsby-code-button-toaster customToasterClass\"\n              data-toaster-text-class=\"gatsby-code-button-toaster-text customToasterTextClass\"\n              data-toaster-text=\"Copied\"\n              data-toaster-duration=\"3500\"\n              onClick=\"copyToClipboard(`composer config repo.<your-name> path <your/path>`, `69286516361667580000`)\"\n            >\n              <div\n                class=\"gatsby-code-button customButtonClass\"\n                data-tooltip=\"\"\n              >\n                Copy<svg class=\"gatsby-code-button-icon\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"><path fill=\"none\" d=\"M0 0h24v24H0V0z\"/><path d=\"M16 1H2v16h2V3h12V1zm-1 4l6 6v12H6V5h9zm-1 7h5.5L14 6.5V12z\"/></svg>\n              </div>\n            </div>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"gatsby-code-bash\"><code class=\"gatsby-code-bash\"><span class=\"token function\">composer</span> config repo.<span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>your-name<span class=\"token operator\">></span> path <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>your/path<span class=\"token operator\">></span></code></pre></div>\n<p>Or in this specific case:</p>\n<div\n              class=\"gatsby-code-button-container\"\n              data-toaster-id=\"53452740619992370000\"\n              data-toaster-class=\"gatsby-code-button-toaster customToasterClass\"\n              data-toaster-text-class=\"gatsby-code-button-toaster-text customToasterTextClass\"\n              data-toaster-text=\"Copied\"\n              data-toaster-duration=\"3500\"\n              onClick=\"copyToClipboard(`composer config repo.store path localmodules/store-graphql/\ncat composer.json # check that there's a store module`, `53452740619992370000`)\"\n            >\n              <div\n                class=\"gatsby-code-button customButtonClass\"\n                data-tooltip=\"\"\n              >\n                Copy<svg class=\"gatsby-code-button-icon\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"><path fill=\"none\" d=\"M0 0h24v24H0V0z\"/><path d=\"M16 1H2v16h2V3h12V1zm-1 4l6 6v12H6V5h9zm-1 7h5.5L14 6.5V12z\"/></svg>\n              </div>\n            </div>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"gatsby-code-bash\"><code class=\"gatsby-code-bash\"><span class=\"token function\">composer</span> config repo.store path localmodules/store-graphql/\n<span class=\"token function\">cat</span> composer.json <span class=\"token comment\"># check that there's a store module</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>So now we need to make sure that store is installed on our local system as a higher version.</p>\n<p>Using a text editor open <code class=\"gatsby-code-text\">src/localmodules/store-graphql</code> open <code class=\"gatsby-code-text\">composer.json</code> file and specify a new version, in this case <code class=\"gatsby-code-text\">1.0.3</code>.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><strong>Note</strong></p>\n<p>Do not commit the <code class=\"gatsby-code-text\">composer.json</code> changes.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Next, let’s update:</p>\n<div\n              class=\"gatsby-code-button-container\"\n              data-toaster-id=\"45737282029434724000\"\n              data-toaster-class=\"gatsby-code-button-toaster customToasterClass\"\n              data-toaster-text-class=\"gatsby-code-button-toaster-text customToasterTextClass\"\n              data-toaster-text=\"Copied\"\n              data-toaster-duration=\"3500\"\n              onClick=\"copyToClipboard(`composer update scandipwa/store-graphql`, `45737282029434724000`)\"\n            >\n              <div\n                class=\"gatsby-code-button customButtonClass\"\n                data-tooltip=\"\"\n              >\n                Copy<svg class=\"gatsby-code-button-icon\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"><path fill=\"none\" d=\"M0 0h24v24H0V0z\"/><path d=\"M16 1H2v16h2V3h12V1zm-1 4l6 6v12H6V5h9zm-1 7h5.5L14 6.5V12z\"/></svg>\n              </div>\n            </div>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"gatsby-code-bash\"><code class=\"gatsby-code-bash\"><span class=\"token function\">composer</span> update scandipwa/store-graphql</code></pre></div>\n<p>After this the <code class=\"gatsby-code-text\">src/localmodules/store-graphql</code> will be symlinked with the vendor folders. This way any change you perform on the origin folder will be reflected in Magento.</p>\n<p>After making changes, <code class=\"gatsby-code-text\">exit</code> the container and go to the <code class=\"gatsby-code-text\">store-graphql</code> directory.</p>\n<div\n              class=\"gatsby-code-button-container\"\n              data-toaster-id=\"67718092380425080000\"\n              data-toaster-class=\"gatsby-code-button-toaster customToasterClass\"\n              data-toaster-text-class=\"gatsby-code-button-toaster-text customToasterTextClass\"\n              data-toaster-text=\"Copied\"\n              data-toaster-duration=\"3500\"\n              onClick=\"copyToClipboard(`cd src/localmodules/store-graphql`, `67718092380425080000`)\"\n            >\n              <div\n                class=\"gatsby-code-button customButtonClass\"\n                data-tooltip=\"\"\n              >\n                Copy<svg class=\"gatsby-code-button-icon\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"><path fill=\"none\" d=\"M0 0h24v24H0V0z\"/><path d=\"M16 1H2v16h2V3h12V1zm-1 4l6 6v12H6V5h9zm-1 7h5.5L14 6.5V12z\"/></svg>\n              </div>\n            </div>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"gatsby-code-bash\"><code class=\"gatsby-code-bash\"><span class=\"token builtin class-name\">cd</span> src/localmodules/store-graphql</code></pre></div>\n<p>We can check out if our changes are registered by using <code class=\"gatsby-code-text\">git status</code>, in fact can use <code class=\"gatsby-code-text\">git status</code> any time to see what the state of our commit is.</p>\n<p>After this we can use a similar sequence as previously:</p>\n<div\n              class=\"gatsby-code-button-container\"\n              data-toaster-id=\"76741851690211160000\"\n              data-toaster-class=\"gatsby-code-button-toaster customToasterClass\"\n              data-toaster-text-class=\"gatsby-code-button-toaster-text customToasterTextClass\"\n              data-toaster-text=\"Copied\"\n              data-toaster-duration=\"3500\"\n              onClick=\"copyToClipboard(`git checkout -b feature-branch-1\ngit add src         # add the whole folder\ngit commit -m &quot;Some message&quot;\ngit push\ngit push origin feature-branch-1`, `76741851690211160000`)\"\n            >\n              <div\n                class=\"gatsby-code-button customButtonClass\"\n                data-tooltip=\"\"\n              >\n                Copy<svg class=\"gatsby-code-button-icon\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"><path fill=\"none\" d=\"M0 0h24v24H0V0z\"/><path d=\"M16 1H2v16h2V3h12V1zm-1 4l6 6v12H6V5h9zm-1 7h5.5L14 6.5V12z\"/></svg>\n              </div>\n            </div>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"gatsby-code-bash\"><code class=\"gatsby-code-bash\"><span class=\"token function\">git</span> checkout -b feature-branch-1\n<span class=\"token function\">git</span> <span class=\"token function\">add</span> src         <span class=\"token comment\"># add the whole folder</span>\n<span class=\"token function\">git</span> commit -m <span class=\"token string\">\"Some message\"</span>\n<span class=\"token function\">git</span> push\n<span class=\"token function\">git</span> push origin feature-branch-1</code></pre></div>\n<p>After this we can go to our GitHub account and open a pull request.</p>","frontmatter":{"title":"How To Contribute"},"fields":{"path":"content/docs/contribute.md","slug":"/docs/contribute.html"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/docs/contribute.html"}},"staticQueryHashes":[]}